      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@djaqeel: Operator overloading makes the code less readable <i>when used badly</i>. When used well, it can greatly enhance readability IMO. Look at code which uses <code>BigInteger</code> in Java, then look at similar code using <code>BigInteger</code> in C# using operators. I don&#39;t see how delegates break OOP principles - you need to be much more precise than that in your objections. I don&#39;t know the details of why the Java designers didn&#39;t include various features, but I suspect there&#39;s a mixture of resource pressure and a desire to keep the language small and relatively simple."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 5827467,
        "reputation" : 6145,
        "user_id" : 4594973,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 71,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/USV9e.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "code_dredd",
