      "comment_id" : 80423511,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I know this is late, but an example is worth a thousand arguments. Given <code>m0</code> as a <code>Matrix</code> and <code>v0</code>, <code>v1</code>, <code>v2</code>, <code>v3</code>, and <code>v4</code> as <code>Vector</code>s, simply compare how long it takes you to <i>correctly</i> interpret the following mathematical expression <code>m0.transpose().mult(v0.add(v1.mult(v2)).cross(v3)).sub(v4);</code>. Had support for operator overloading been included, it could&#39;ve been written as <code>m0.transpose() * (v0 + v1 * v2).cross(v3) - v4;</code>."
    }, {
